abstract.description: abstract of the item (e.g. the abstract of a journal article)

annote.description: reader's notes about the item content

archive_location.description: storage location within an archive (e.g. a box and folder number)

authority.description: issuing or judicial authority (e.g. "USPTO" for a patent, "Fairfax Circuit Court" for a legal case)

call-number.description: call number (to locate the item in a library)

citation-label.description: label identifying the item in in-text citations of label styles (e.g. "Ferr78"). May be assigned by the CSL processor based on item metadata.

citation-number.description: index (starting at 1) of the cited reference in the bibliography (generated by the CSL processor)

collection-title.description: title of the collection holding the item (e.g. the series title for a book)

container-title.description: title of the container holding the item (e.g. the book title for a book chapter, the journal title for a journal article)

container-title-short.description: short/abbreviated form of "container-title" (also accessible through the "short" form of the "container-title" variable)

dimensions.description: physical (e.g. size) or temporal (e.g. running time) dimensions of the item

event.description: name of the related event (e.g. the conference name when citing a conference paper)

event-place.description: geographic location of the related event (e.g. "Amsterdam, the Netherlands")

first-reference-note-number.description: number of a preceding note containing the first reference to the item. Assigned by the CSL processor. The variable holds no value for non-note-based styles, or when the item hasn't been cited in any preceding notes.

genre.description: class, type or genre of the item (e.g. "adventure" for an adventure movie, "PhD dissertation" for a PhD thesis)

jurisdiction.description: geographic scope of relevance (e.g. "US" for a US patent)

keyword.description: keyword(s) or tag(s) attached to the item

locator.description: a cite-specific pinpointer within the item (e.g. a page number within a book, or a volume in a multi-volume work). Must be accompanied in the input data by a label indicating the locator type (see the Locators term list), which determines which term is rendered by cs:label when the "locator" variable is selected.

note.description: (short) inline note giving additional item details (e.g. a concise summary or commentary)

original-publisher.description: original publisher, for items that have been republished by a different publisher

original-publisher-place.description: geographic location of the original publisher (e.g. "London, UK")

original-title.description: title of the original version (e.g. "Война и мир", the untranslated Russian title of "War and Peace")

page.description: range of pages the item (e.g. a journal article) covers in a container (e.g. a journal issue)

page-first.description: first page of the range of pages the item (e.g. a journal article) covers in a container (e.g. a journal issue)

references.description: resources related to the procedural history of a legal case

reviewed-title.description: title of the item reviewed by the current item

section.description: container section holding the item (e.g. "politics" for a newspaper article)

source.description: from whence the item originates (e.g. a library catalog or database)

title-short.description: short/abbreviated form of "title" (also accessible through the "short" form of the "title" variable)

version.description: version of the item (e.g. "2.0.9" for a software program)

year-suffix.description: disambiguating year suffix in author-date styles (e.g. "a" in "Doe, 1999a")

collection-number.description: number identifying the collection holding the item (e.g. the series number for a book)

edition.description: (container) edition holding the item (e.g. "3" when citing a chapter in the third edition of a book)

issue.description: (container) issue holding the item (e.g. "5" when citing a journal article from journal volume 2, issue 5)

number.description: number identifying the item (e.g. a report number)

number-of-pages.description: total number of pages of the cited item

number-of-volumes.description: total number of volumes, usable for citing multi-volume books and such

volume.description: (container) volume holding the item (e.g. "2" when citing a chapter from book volume 2)

accessed.description: date the item has been accessed

event-date.description: date the related event took place

submitted.description: date the item (e.g. a manuscript) has been submitted for publication

collection-editor.description: editor of the collection holding the item (e.g. the series editor for a book)

container-author.description: author of the container holding the item (e.g. the book author for a book chapter)

editorial-director.description: managing editor ("Directeur de la Publication" in French)

reviewed-author.description: author of the item reviewed by the current item

language.description: Language code. Not intended for display purposes.
